								<!-- bodycontent -->
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="dablink">For other people named Robert Wilson, see <a href="Robert_Wilson_(disambiguation)" title="Robert Wilson (disambiguation)" class="mw-redirect">Robert Wilson (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<table class="infobox biography vcard" cellspacing="3" style="border-spacing: 3px; width:22em;">
<tr>
<th colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center; font-size:125%; font-weight:bold;"><span class="fn">Robert Wilson</span></th>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Born</th>
<td class="" style=""><span style="display:none">(<span class="bday">1941-10-04</span>)</span> October 4, 1941 <span class="noprint ForceAgeToShow">(age&#160;71)</span><br />
<span class="birthplace"><a href="Waco,_Texas" title="Waco, Texas">Waco, Texas</a>, <a href="United_States" title="United States">USA</a></span></td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Occupation</th>
<td class="role" style=""><a href="Theatre_director" title="Theatre director">Theatre director</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center;">Website</th>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<td colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center;"><a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://robertwilson.com/">http://robertwilson.com/</a></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Robert Wilson</b> (born 4 October 1941) is an <a href="United_States_of_America" title="United States of America" class="mw-redirect">American</a> <a href="Avant-garde" title="Avant-garde">avant-garde</a> <a href="Stage_director" title="Stage director" class="mw-redirect">stage director</a> and <a href="Playwright" title="Playwright">playwright</a> who has been called "[America]'s — or even the world's — foremost vanguard 'theater artist'".<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> Over the course of his wide-ranging career, he has also worked as a <a href="Choreographer" title="Choreographer" class="mw-redirect">choreographer</a>, <a href="Performer" title="Performer" class="mw-redirect">performer</a>, <a href="Painting" title="Painting">painter</a>, <a href="Sculptor" title="Sculptor" class="mw-redirect">sculptor</a>, <a href="Video_artist" title="Video artist" class="mw-redirect">video artist</a>, and <a href="Sound" title="Sound">sound</a> and <a href="Lighting_designer" title="Lighting designer">lighting designer</a>. He is best known for his collaborations with <a href="Philip_Glass" title="Philip Glass">Philip Glass</a> on <i><a href="Einstein_on_the_Beach" title="Einstein on the Beach">Einstein on the Beach</a></i>, and with numerous other artists, including <a href="Heiner_M%C3%BCller" title="Heiner Müller">Heiner Müller</a>, <a href="../William_S._Burroughs" title="William S. Burroughs">William S. Burroughs</a>, <a href="Allen_Ginsberg" title="Allen Ginsberg">Allen Ginsberg</a>, <a href="Lou_Reed" title="Lou Reed">Lou Reed</a>, <a href="Tom_Waits" title="Tom Waits">Tom Waits</a>, <a href="David_Byrne_(musician)" title="David Byrne (musician)" class="mw-redirect">David Byrne</a>, <a href="Laurie_Anderson" title="Laurie Anderson">Laurie Anderson</a>, <a href="Gavin_Bryars" title="Gavin Bryars">Gavin Bryars</a>, <a href="Rufus_Wainwright" title="Rufus Wainwright">Rufus Wainwright</a> and <a href="Marina_Abramovic" title="Marina Abramovic" class="mw-redirect">Marina Abramovic</a>.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc">
